<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-BIG-12-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUTTON RIPS REFS OVER TECHNICAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JIMMY BURCH AND MIKE JONES 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Oklahoma State coach Eddie Sutton chastised
game officials for calling a technical foul on the Cowboys' bench
with 8:05 remaining in a game that was tied, 49-49. After a foul
was called underneath the Iowa State basket, several players and
student managers seated on the Cowboys' bench joined Sutton in
standing as the coach bellowed his disapproval of the call.
</P>
<P>
   From the opposite end of the court, referee Bob Sitov pointed at
the Oklahoma State bench and assessed the technical, much to
Sutton's surprise. Sutton characterized the call as nitpicking and
said he sought an explanation from Dale Kelley, Big 12 men's
coordinator of basketball officials.
</P>
<P>
   ``You would think in a league with four teams in the Top 20,
there should be better officiating than what was out there this
afternoon,'' said Sutton, whose team lost to Iowa State, 68-64.
``I'm sure I'll get reprimanded for saying this ... But how can you
call a technical foul on guys for standing up? How can you make
that call in a big-time game? If someone says something, OK. But
not that. I want an explanation from Dale Kelley.''
</P>
<P>
   During the final 2:20, three Oklahoma State starters fouled out
as the Cowboys watched a 61-57 lead disappear. Asked his assessment
of the officiating other than the technical foul, Sutton smiled and
remained silent for several seconds.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've probably said enough already,'' he said.  &LR; name: _ Jimmy
Burch \Nsubheds:Loss upsets Mihm Texas center Chris Mihm admitted
profound disappointment in the way the Longhorns lost their
semifinal game against Oklahoma, but tried to find a reason for
optimism.
</P>
<P>
   ``Actually, in the long run this might be the slap in the face
to wake us up and get us ready for the NCAA Tournament,'' he said.
``That's what I'm hoping. Last year we were inexperienced in
postseason and we had some first-timers here today. Hopefully this
will show them what it's like, that it's do or die, one loss and
you're out. That's what I'm hoping.''  &LR; name: _ Mike Jones
\Nsubheds:Sutton: ISU deserves top seed Iowa State coach Larry
