championship game, remained noncommittal when asked about the
Cyclones' probable seeding in the NCAA tournament. But not Oklahoma
State coach Eddie Sutton, whose team fell to Iowa State in
yesterday's semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   ``If they win \Rtoday\S, they ought to get a No. 1 seed,''
Sutton said. ``They won the regular-season title. They'd be 29-4.
The NCAA tournament committee should give them a top seed.''
</P>
<P>
   Sutton said the season-ending injury to Cincinnati forward
Kenyon Martin, coupled with the Bearcats' early exit from the
Conference USA tournament, should open up a top seed for Iowa
State. At worst, said Sutton, the Cyclones deserve a No. 2 seed.
