No. 4 seed, or somewhere in that area. But I will be disappointed
if the winner of \Rthe Big 12 tournament\S doesn't get a No. 2
seed. I want to see this league continue to grow and I'm not sure
we have the national respect we deserve. But we'll have to \Rget\S
that in the tournament.''
