   LEWIS-BEHAVIOR _ Nothing is more predictable in a case like the
one involving football star Ray Lewis than this: Eyewitness
accounts will vary. ``That's the problem with a chaotic, dimly lit
scene,'' said defense attorney Jack Martin. ``It would be more
suspicious if everyone had the same story.'' And the stories do
vary widely in the case of the street melee that occurred in the
early morning hours after the Super Bowl near a Buckhead nightclub,
leaving two men, Jacinth Baker and Richard Lollar, stabbed to
death. (Torpy, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED in (a) General
News and (s) Sports categories.
