   In Chicago, the Smell &AMP; Taste Treatment and Research Foundation
has released results of a survey that determined that people who
smell and eat garlic bread at dinner make fewer negative and more
positive comments about family members.
</P>
<P>
   According to Foundation head  &UR; Alan Hirsch &LR; , business meetings
and political debates might be facilitated by the serving of garlic
bread.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SANTANA AND SMELL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In a Rolling Stone interview,  &UR; Carlos Santana &LR;  says that he has
visions and speaks to spirits and that his sense of smell has
