   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   FLANNERY-O'CONNOR-YEAR _ She likely would have thought it silly,
but they're naming a year after her, anyway. In Milledgeville,
where she grew up, studied, and wrote many of her most enduring
works, 2000 is ``The Year of Flannery O'Connor.'' The declaration
was made by Georgia College &AMP; State University, O'Connor's alma
mater. Throughout this year, the school is sponsoring a variety of
events celebrating the life and themes of the famous writer.
(Osinski, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TV-ONCEAGAIN _ Commentary: When ``Once and Again'' debuted it
looked like a show about two divorced people falling in love. Over
its first season, it's morphed into a provocative and deeply felt
meditation on family. Ratings, however, haven't kept up with the
changes. A look at the show, keyed to tonight's episode. (Kloer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   DANGELO _ D'Angelo, the guy who reintroduced soul and live
musicianship to R&AMP;B music five years ago, plays the first of two
shows at the Fox Theatre tonight. We explain how this 25-year-old
with only two albums under his belt has managed to: lay a pathway
for the Maxwell and Lauryn Hills that followed his debut; attract
an older audience with his Marvin Gaye feel; receive airplay on
varying formats of radio (R&AMP;B, pop, rap and jazz) _all while his
current album ``Voodoo'' snags the no. 1 pop position atop Britney
Spears and Celine Dion. (With a little help from his seemingly
naked body in current music video, ``Untitled''). (SoMurray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   DVD _ The handwriting is on the wall, and so are the DVDs. About
18 months ago, retail stores and video rental shops had shelf after
shelf of videotapes for sale or rent. If they carried DVDs at all,
the ratio was usually about 20 videotapes to every one DVD. Now the
shelf space ratio is down to about three to one in favor of
videotape. And don't be surprised if the margin tips in favor of
DVD in another 18 months. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 34. MOVED.
WITH PHOTOS and a GRAPHIC.
</P>
