<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, March 13 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
please contact Dennis Liff at the Daily News at (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   RAMPART-REHABILITATE (Los Angeles) _ The foot-long CRASH sign on
the dark blue door of Rampart Division's anti-gang unit recently
came down, symbolizing the LAPD's effort to remove the stain of
scandal left by rogue officers who may have sent hundreds of
innocent people to jail. What's not so simple is to rehabilitate an
entire division. That job is going to Robert B. Hansohn, a 29-year
veteran with five commands in his dossier. By Greg Gittrich and
Beth Barrett. (Will run in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
