   (NYT4) WASHINGTON -- March 12, 2000 -- RICHARDSON-PROFILE --
Energy Secretary Bill Richardson, 52, the only Hispanic in the
Cabinet, is a former Democratic House leader from New Mexico with
appeal to the Latino voters who are being heavily recruited by both
parties in the presidential race. While Richardson campaigned for
Vice President Al Gore in Iowa, New Hampshire and California, often
before Hispanic audiences, he insists he has no designs on the
Democratic ticket. ``We haven't talked about the vice presidency,
and I'm not campaigning for it,'' he says. (Shana Raab/The New York
Times)
