<P>
   (NYT2) HERNDON, Va. -- March 12, 2000 -- PSI-NET -- PSINet, with
fiber-optic lines around the globe, some of the world's most
advanced Internet systems and a fast-growing customer base, looms
as a highly attractive acquisition candidate. It is the biggest of
the Internet access providers not already snatched up by telephone
companies looking to expand into cyberspace. Pete Wills, president,
left, and William L. Schrader, chairman of PSINet Inc, in the
company's Herndon hosting facility in Herndon, Va. (Marty Katz/The
New York Times)
