   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- March 12, 2000 -- JOY-CONCERNS -- Breaking
ranks with the customarily optimistic and self-congratulatory
high-technology industry, Bill Joy, the chief scientist of Sun
Microsystems, has issued an impassioned critique of uncontrolled
progress in digital, biological and material sciences. He has
challenged scientists and engineers to rethink their ethical
standards and step back from advances that might ultimately
threaten the human species. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
