<P>
   &QL; 
CANADA (Phoenix) _ Canadian ``snowbirds'' always come back to
Arizona like swallows returning to Capistrano. Or do they? The slow
business in Phoenix's East Valley winter visitor RV parks this year
is blamed in part on the change in the migratory pattern of
Canadians. Some are traveling past Arizona to newer and cheaper
places in Mexico while others are staying in Canada and migrating
to British Columbia, where the weather is moderate, Canadians
remain covered by Canada's public health-care system and there's no
devaluation of currency as occurs across the U.S. line. By MAUREEN
